The main part of the Template Designer application window consists of the graphical editor. This chapter describes its components and how to use them.

## Designer View
The Designer View of Doxee Template Designer is the panel where WYSIWYG editing of the templates is performed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 44. switch between Designer and PDF Preview*

## PDF Preview
The PDF (FOP) tab previews the document using the sample XML data defined in the Data Inputs of the template. By default FOP is used as PDF renderer. In the preferences, the FOP configuration can be specified, or other renderers like XMLMIND, XEP, or IBEX can be activated (see [FO](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-actions-1-1#fo)).

In order to be able to display a PDF preview a sample data input is needed as soon as any dynamic data refers to it in the template.

## XSLT Preview
By activating Show XSLT in the Preferences (see [XSL-FO](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-actions-1-1#xslfo) and [XSL-IDX](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-actions-1-1#xslidx)) additional tabs can be added to the Main View where the generated XSL-FO code is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 45. Main &gt; XSLT Preview*

## FO Preview
By activating Show FO in the Preferences (see [FO](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-actions-1-1#fo)) an additional tab is added to the Main View where the generated FO code is displayed.

## Palette
The Palette is available in the Template Designer editor to provide easy access to all elements. The palette is grouped into several drawers.

##### Standard
comprises all plain content and structuring elements such as Text, Image, Table or List as well as specialized elements like Barcode or Static Page Content.

##### Forms
contains form elements used to create PDF forms, e.g. inputs fields, radio buttons, etc.

##### Dynamic
contains all elements which are used to display and manipulate dynamic data respectively process them with logical constraints or loops.

##### Building Blocks
contains reusable elements for documents, like template parts or external references to other Infinica Templates.

Elements from the Palette can easily be placed in the template. They can either be placed by drag and drop to the desired destination or by having the cursor set to a valid template position, which is available for insertion of that specific element, followed by a double-click in the palette.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 46. Main &gt; Designer &gt; Palette*

See [Elements](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-template-designer-user-guide-elements-1-1) for more information about the available elements.
